In the Matter of NASSAU PRESS, INCORPORATED, Bankrupt. LONG ISLAND NATIONAL BANK, Petitioner-Appellant, Sidney GREGORY, Trustee in Bankruptcy of Nassau Press, Incorporated, Respondent-Appellee. No. 21, Docket 30431. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued Sept. 27, 1966. Decided Oct. 13, 1966. Bernard Jeffrey, Freeport, N. Y. (Mul-looly, Mullen & Jeffrey, Freeport, N. Y.), for appellant. John G. Crowe (Ridgway, Ridgway & Slote, New York City), for appellee.

Before MOORE, FRIENDLY and KAUFMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the opinion of Judge Mishler, 259 F.Supp. 666, E.D.N.Y.1966.
